<Page x:Class="SWAN.Views.WikiPages.SA4WikiPage"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      Title="WikiPage"  
      Background="{DynamicResource ApplicationBackgroundBrush}"
  Foreground="{DynamicResource TextFillColorPrimaryBrush}">

    <!-- Ensure FlowDocumentReader stretches to fill available space -->
    <FlowDocumentScrollViewer x:Name="flowDocumentScrollViewer" Width="auto" Height="auto" HorizontalContentAlignment="Stretch">
        <FlowDocument x:Name="flowDocument" IsOptimalParagraphEnabled="True" IsHyphenationEnabled="True">
            <!-- Center-align the title to take up the entire frame width -->
            <Paragraph FontSize="30">

                <Run Text="SA-4: Acquisition Process " FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>

            <!-- Left-align content -->
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Left">
                <Run Text="Severity :" FontWeight="ExtraBold"/>
                <Run Text="High" FontWeight="ExtraBold" Foreground="Red"/>
                <Run Text="-" FontWeight="ExtraBold" Foreground="Red"/>
                <Run Text="High" FontWeight="ExtraBold" Foreground="Red"/>
            </Paragraph>
            <!-- Add more content as needed -->
            <Paragraph FontSize="30">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Control Extension" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            
            <!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE FOR PHYSICAL CONTROL -->
            <Paragraph Margin="10,20,0,0" Tag="SA4numberone">
                <Run Text="1." FontWeight="ExtraBold" FontSize="30"></Run>
                The developer shall document the software/firmware security requirements in a Software Requirements Specification or equivalent document
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Left" Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <Run Text="Maps To:"  FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="15" ></Run>
                <Run Text="CCI- 003095, CCI-003096"  FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="15" ></Run>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                The organization includes the security strength requirements, explicitly or by reference, in the acquisition contract for the information system, system component, or information system service in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, standards, guidelines, and organizational mission/business needs.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Implementation Guidance" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                The organization being inspected/assessed documents within contracts/agreements for the information system, system component, or information system service, the security strength requirements, explicitly or by reference, IAW DoDI 8580.1.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Validation Procedures" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                The organization conducting the inspection/assessment obtains and examines the contracts/agreements to ensure the organization being inspected/assessed includes the security strength requirements, explicitly or by reference, in the acquisition contract for the information system, system component, or information system service in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, standards, guidelines, and organizational mission/business needs including DoDI 8580.1.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Compelling Evidence" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                Acquisition contract includes security strength requirements and documents compliance with laws and regulations, as well as organizational mission/business needs.
            </Paragraph>

            <!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE FOR PHYSICAL CONTROL -->
            <Paragraph Margin="10,20,0,0" Tag="SA4numbertwo">
                <Run Text="2." FontWeight="ExtraBold" FontSize="30"></Run>
                The developer shall provide, explicitly or by reference, a description of   the functional properties of the software/firmware security controls to be employed.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Left" Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <Run Text="Maps To:"  FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="15" ></Run>
                <Run Text="CCI-003094"  FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="15" ></Run>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                The organization includes the security functional requirements, explicitly or by reference, in the acquisition contract for the information system, system component, or information system service in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, standards, guidelines, and organizational mission/business needs.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Implementation Guidance" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                The organization being inspected/assessed documents within contracts/agreements for the information system, system component, or information system service, the security functional requirements, explicitly or by reference, IAW DoDI 8580.1.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Validation Procedures" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                The organization conducting the inspection/assessment obtains and examines the contracts/agreements to ensure the organization being inspected/assessed includes the security functional requirements, explicitly or by reference, in the acquisition contract for the information system, system component, or information system service in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, standards, guidelines, and organizational mission/business needs including DoDI 8580.1.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="50,20,0,0">
                <LineBreak></LineBreak>
                <Run Text="Compelling Evidence" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="30" />
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph Margin="70,20,0,0">
                Acquisition contract includes security functional requirements and documents compliance with laws and regulations, as well as organizational mission/business needs.
            </Paragraph>

        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentScrollViewer>
</Page>
